15#ifndef DNS_TKEY_H
16#define DNS_TKEY_H 1
17
18/*! \file dns/tkey.h */
19
20#include <inttypes.h>
21#include <stdbool.h>
22
23#include <isc/lang.h>
24
25#include <dns/types.h>
26
27#include <dst/dst.h>
28#include <dst/gssapi.h>
29
30ISC_LANG_BEGINDECLS
31
32/* Key agreement modes */
33#define DNS_TKEYMODE_SERVERASSIGNED 1
34#define DNS_TKEYMODE_DIFFIEHELLMAN 2
35#define DNS_TKEYMODE_GSSAPI 3
36#define DNS_TKEYMODE_RESOLVERASSIGNED 4
37#define DNS_TKEYMODE_DELETE 5
38
39struct dns_tkeyctx {
40 dst_key_t *dhkey;
41 dns_name_t *domain;
42 gss_cred_id_t gsscred;
43 isc_mem_t *mctx;
44 char *gssapi_keytab;
45};
46
47isc_result_t
48dns_tkeyctx_create(isc_mem_t *mctx, dns_tkeyctx_t **tctxp);
49/*%<
50 * Create an empty TKEY context.
51 *
52 * Requires:
53 *\li 'mctx' is not NULL
54 *\li 'tctx' is not NULL
55 *\li '*tctx' is NULL
56 *
57 * Returns
58 *\li #ISC_R_SUCCESS
59 *\li #ISC_R_NOMEMORY
60 *\li return codes from dns_name_fromtext()
61 */
62
63void
64dns_tkeyctx_destroy(dns_tkeyctx_t **tctxp);
65/*%<
66 * Frees all data associated with the TKEY context
67 *
68 * Requires:
69 *\li 'tctx' is not NULL
70 *\li '*tctx' is not NULL
71 */
72
73isc_result_t
74dns_tkey_processquery(dns_message_t *msg, dns_tkeyctx_t *tctx,
75 dns_tsig_keyring_t *ring);
76/*%<
77 * Processes a query containing a TKEY record, adding or deleting TSIG
78 * keys if necessary, and modifies the message to contain the response.
79 *
80 * Requires:
81 *\li 'msg' is a valid message
82 *\li 'tctx' is a valid TKEY context
83 *\li 'ring' is a valid TSIG keyring
84 *
85 * Returns
86 *\li #ISC_R_SUCCESS msg was updated (the TKEY operation succeeded,
87 * or msg now includes a TKEY with an error set)
88 * DNS_R_FORMERR the packet was malformed (missing a TKEY
89 * or KEY).
90 *\li other An error occurred while processing the message
91 */
92
93isc_result_t
94dns_tkey_builddhquery(dns_message_t *msg, dst_key_t *key,
95 const dns_name_t *name, const dns_name_t *algorithm,
96 isc_buffer_t *nonce, uint32_t lifetime);
97/*%<
98 * Builds a query containing a TKEY that will generate a shared
99 * secret using a Diffie-Hellman key exchange. The shared key
100 * will be of the specified algorithm (only DNS_TSIG_HMACMD5_NAME
101 * is supported), and will be named either 'name',
102 * 'name' + server chosen domain, or random data + server chosen domain
103 * if 'name' == dns_rootname. If nonce is not NULL, it supplies
104 * random data used in the shared secret computation. The key is
105 * requested to have the specified lifetime (in seconds)
106 *
107 *
108 * Requires:
109 *\li 'msg' is a valid message
110 *\li 'key' is a valid Diffie Hellman dst key
111 *\li 'name' is a valid name
112 *\li 'algorithm' is a valid name
113 *
114 * Returns:
115 *\li #ISC_R_SUCCESS msg was successfully updated to include the
116 * query to be sent
117 *\li other an error occurred while building the message
118 */
119
120isc_result_t
121dns_tkey_buildgssquery(dns_message_t *msg, const dns_name_t *name,
122 const dns_name_t *gname, isc_buffer_t *intoken,
123 uint32_t lifetime, gss_ctx_id_t *context,
124 bool win2k, isc_mem_t *mctx,
125 char **err_message);
126/*%<
127 * Builds a query containing a TKEY that will generate a GSSAPI context.
128 * The key is requested to have the specified lifetime (in seconds).
129 *
130 * Requires:
131 *\li 'msg' is a valid message
132 *\li 'name' is a valid name
133 *\li 'gname' is a valid name
134 *\li 'context' is a pointer to a valid gss_ctx_id_t
135 * (which may have the value GSS_C_NO_CONTEXT)
136 *\li 'win2k' when true says to turn on some hacks to work
137 * with the non-standard GSS-TSIG of Windows 2000
138 *
139 * Returns:
140 *\li ISC_R_SUCCESS msg was successfully updated to include the
141 * query to be sent
142 *\li other an error occurred while building the message
143 *\li *err_message optional error message
144 */
145
146
147isc_result_t
148dns_tkey_builddeletequery(dns_message_t *msg, dns_tsigkey_t *key);
149/*%<
150 * Builds a query containing a TKEY record that will delete the
151 * specified shared secret from the server.
152 *
153 * Requires:
154 *\li 'msg' is a valid message
155 *\li 'key' is a valid TSIG key
156 *
157 * Returns:
158 *\li #ISC_R_SUCCESS msg was successfully updated to include the
159 * query to be sent
160 *\li other an error occurred while building the message
161 */
162
163isc_result_t
164dns_tkey_processdhresponse(dns_message_t *qmsg, dns_message_t *rmsg,
165 dst_key_t *key, isc_buffer_t *nonce,
166 dns_tsigkey_t **outkey, dns_tsig_keyring_t *ring);
167/*%<
168 * Processes a response to a query containing a TKEY that was
169 * designed to generate a shared secret using a Diffie-Hellman key
170 * exchange. If the query was successful, a new shared key
171 * is created and added to the list of shared keys.
172 *
173 * Requires:
174 *\li 'qmsg' is a valid message (the query)
175 *\li 'rmsg' is a valid message (the response)
176 *\li 'key' is a valid Diffie Hellman dst key
177 *\li 'outkey' is either NULL or a pointer to NULL
178 *\li 'ring' is a valid keyring or NULL
179 *
180 * Returns:
181 *\li #ISC_R_SUCCESS the shared key was successfully added
182 *\li #ISC_R_NOTFOUND an error occurred while looking for a
183 * component of the query or response
184 */
185
186isc_result_t
187dns_tkey_processgssresponse(dns_message_t *qmsg, dns_message_t *rmsg,
188 const dns_name_t *gname, gss_ctx_id_t *context,
189 isc_buffer_t *outtoken, dns_tsigkey_t **outkey,
190 dns_tsig_keyring_t *ring, char **err_message);
191/*%<
192 * XXX
193 */
194
195isc_result_t
196dns_tkey_processdeleteresponse(dns_message_t *qmsg, dns_message_t *rmsg,
197 dns_tsig_keyring_t *ring);
198/*%<
199 * Processes a response to a query containing a TKEY that was
200 * designed to delete a shared secret. If the query was successful,
201 * the shared key is deleted from the list of shared keys.
202 *
203 * Requires:
204 *\li 'qmsg' is a valid message (the query)
205 *\li 'rmsg' is a valid message (the response)
206 *\li 'ring' is not NULL
207 *
208 * Returns:
209 *\li #ISC_R_SUCCESS the shared key was successfully deleted
210 *\li #ISC_R_NOTFOUND an error occurred while looking for a
211 * component of the query or response
212 */
213
214isc_result_t
215dns_tkey_gssnegotiate(dns_message_t *qmsg, dns_message_t *rmsg,
216 const dns_name_t *server, gss_ctx_id_t *context,
217 dns_tsigkey_t **outkey, dns_tsig_keyring_t *ring,
218 bool win2k, char **err_message);
219
220/*
221 * Client side negotiation of GSS-TSIG. Process the response
222 * to a TKEY, and establish a TSIG key if negotiation was successful.
223 * Build a response to the input TKEY message. Can take multiple
224 * calls to successfully establish the context.
225 *
226 * Requires:
227 * 'qmsg' is a valid message, the original TKEY request;
228 * it will be filled with the new message to send
229 * 'rmsg' is a valid message, the incoming TKEY message
230 * 'server' is the server name
231 * 'context' is the input context handle
232 * 'outkey' receives the established key, if non-NULL;
233 * if non-NULL must point to NULL
234 * 'ring' is the keyring in which to establish the key,
235 * or NULL
236 * 'win2k' when true says to turn on some hacks to work
237 * with the non-standard GSS-TSIG of Windows 2000
238 *
239 * Returns:
240 * ISC_R_SUCCESS context was successfully established
241 * ISC_R_NOTFOUND couldn't find a needed part of the query
242 * or response
243 * DNS_R_CONTINUE additional context negotiation is required;
244 * send the new qmsg to the server
245 */
246
247ISC_LANG_ENDDECLS
248
249#endif /* DNS_TKEY_H */
